&lt;p&gt;OK, I could check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The logo animation seems fine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As for the errors, some are normal (due to the YouTube video), but there are also many errors caused by mixed content — this happens when your page loads both HTTP and HTTPS resources.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your case, it looks like some content is still being loaded from http://giannisk14.sg-host.com, which is likely left over from a domain change or migration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quick fix: Make sure all URLs on your site are updated to use HTTPS. You can use a plugin like &lt;a href=&quot;https://wordpress.org/plugins/better-search-replace/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Better Search Replace&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to scan your database and replace http://giannisk14.sg-host.com with your correct HTTPS domain&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I hope it will help!&lt;/p&gt;

