&lt;p&gt;Hi there,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After some debugging, I was able to isolate the issue. It turns out that when a featured image is missing, an error is triggered that causes the site to crash. This is likely due to a high PHP debug level being active. But for some reason, even if WP_DEBUG enabled there was not more info available...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To get the site working again, I moved all your event posts to the trash (you can restore them at any time) and added a featured image to the remaining event post. The site now loads properly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That said, there&#039;s also an error being thrown when saving the event post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#039;ll be working today on cleaning up these debug messages. In general, such issues shouldn’t occur on a production website and are better suited to a development environment where verbose error reporting is useful.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If possible, I recommend lowering the PHP error reporting level on your server for the production environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’ll release an update for the theme — and most likely for the Wolf Core plugin as well — later today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your patience!&lt;/p&gt;
