&lt;p&gt;I finally found the issue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I noticed that Elementor Pro is overriding the theme&#039;s header, which is why the offcanvas div (and the rest of the markup from header.php) is missing. To fix this, you need to disable Elementor’s custom header and use the theme’s built-in menu instead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Go to&lt;/strong&gt; WordPress Dashboard &amp;gt; &lt;strong&gt;Templates &amp;gt; Theme Builder&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on the &lt;strong&gt;Header&lt;/strong&gt; tab.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Locate the active Elementor header template and click &lt;strong&gt;Edit&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the top left corner, click &lt;strong&gt;&quot;Update&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, then go to &lt;strong&gt;Display Conditions&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove all conditions by clicking the &lt;strong&gt;&quot;X&quot;&lt;/strong&gt; next to them and save.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Alternatively, you can &lt;strong&gt;delete&lt;/strong&gt; the header template from the Theme Builder.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Clear your site cache (if using a caching plugin).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to &lt;strong&gt;Appearance &amp;gt; Menus&lt;/strong&gt; and ensure your primary menu is assigned to the correct location.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reload your site, and the theme’s menu should be back!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;I hope it will help.&lt;/p&gt;

