&lt;p&gt;OK, indeed not sure why it is not displayed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the price filter widget isn’t appearing on the shop page, it’s often because WooCommerce needs to refresh some of its internal data related to product prices and filters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s how you can fix it:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go to &lt;strong&gt;WooCommerce &amp;gt; Status&lt;/strong&gt; in your WordPress dashboard&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click the &lt;strong&gt;“Tools”&lt;/strong&gt; tab at the top&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Run the following tools by clicking their buttons:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build product lookup tables&lt;/strong&gt; → Click &lt;strong&gt;Regenerate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recount terms&lt;/strong&gt; → Click &lt;strong&gt;Recount terms&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regenerate product attributes lookup table&lt;/strong&gt; → Select an attribute (or leave it blank to apply to all), then click &lt;strong&gt;Regenerate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;These steps will refresh WooCommerce&#039;s filtering system so the price filter widget can appear correctly on the shop page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I hope it will help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Best&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PS: I couldn&#039;t do it myself as your admin is in Danish and I didn&#039;t want to mess up anything&lt;/p&gt;

